column598: Find the one who has a dominant strategy and extrapolate what those whose decisions depend on that one will do.

I figured out which player had the dominant strategy and worked backwards from there to figure out what would maximize my payoff by predicting what each player would choose to maximize their payoffs. If I had the dominant strategy then I picked that.

I simply trace the panels until I find one where both numbers in a horizontal column is higher then that of the other. By finding that  I know that person will certainly choose the column with the higher numbers  hence I will use his decision to trace back to my panel and choose from my columns the one that will yield the highest amount of points
I mean what i do is that just see the which row or coloumn gets the highest number. Then  I also need to check the number in other colors to see what my partners likely to choose. |  |

See which color would have only one option to maximize their profit  then work backwards from there to see what other possible colors would choose based on that choice  then make my choice based on that.

First  I checked if one of my two rows had both numbers being greater than the other row. If so  I chose the row with the greater numbers. | If not  I checked what the color to my right would have chosen using the same concept as first step. I repeated this until I figured out what the color to my right would choose. | Then  I chose what would give me the ghier number based on what the color on the right would choose.

I looked at which color will be choosing X or Y no matter what the player that he depends on chooses  as both boxes for X will be greater than those of Y no matter what. Then  I looked at what the player after him will choose  until I got to my color. Most of the time it worked well unless some other color messed up the system.

I searched for the 2x2 box where both possibilities for one option resulted in a higher payoff than either possibility for the other option (there was always at least one such box). I assumed that the player would choose the better option  then followed which option the other players would choose if they used logic based on the same assumption. This usually worked  although sometimes other players either selected randomly or used incorrect logic.

Regressed through each players answer choice until a clear all win answer was evident (IE player would get maximum returns from one obvious choice) and predicted each players choice to maximize my own choice
I tried to figure out what other people would pick  and make my best decision based off the options that left me.
Look at my options. then at the other color in my box. sometimes at all the boxes
Plotting out what the choices the other players might make based on what's most beneficial to them.
